<div id="main-article" class="article-content retro-folders">
<p></p><div class="quoteright" style="width:240px;"><div class="lazy_load_img_box" style="padding-top:140.42%"><img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/images/hoshizoraimage_7249.jpg" class="embeddedimage" border="0" alt="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/images/hoshizoraimage_7249.jpg" width="240" height="337"></div></div><div class="acaptionright" style="width:240px;"> It's like the <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/YouGottaHaveBlueHair" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/YouGottaHaveBlueHair">colors of the rainbow</a>...</div><div class="proper-ad-unit mobile-ad square_ad"><h6 class="ad-caption">Advertisement:</h6><div id="proper-ad-tvtropes_mobile_ad_1"><script>propertag.cmd.push(function() { proper_display('tvtropes_mobile_ad_1'); })</script></div></div><p>Kazuma Hoshino and his little brother Ayumu are moving to the countryside, to the small town of Yamabiko. Ayumu is sickly, and some country air will do him good. As they try to reach the Yoruzuyo Inn, the place where they'll be staying, Ayumu's hat is stolen by a monkey, leading to Kazuma to chase it down. In the process, he runs into Ui Nakatsugawa, and the two accidentally kiss. The next day, Kazuma discovers that Ui in his class, signaling the start of an exciting new life.</p><p>Originally a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/VisualNovel" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/VisualNovel">Visual Novel</a> by Feng (creators of <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VisualNovel/AkaneIroNiSomaruSaka" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VisualNovel/AkaneIroNiSomaruSaka">Akane-iro ni Somaru Saka</a></em>), <em>A Bridge to the Starry Skies</em> (<em>Hoshizora e Kakaru Hashi</em>) was adapted into an anime in the <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Spring2011Anime" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Spring2011Anime">spring of 2011</a>.</p><p>US viewers may watch the anime legally at <a class="urllink" href="http://www.crunchyroll.com/a-bridge-to-the-starry-skies-hoshizora-e-kakaru-hashi">Crunchyroll.<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a></p><p></p><hr><div class="proper-ad-unit mobile-ad square_ad"><h6 class="ad-caption">Advertisement:</h6><div id="proper-ad-tvtropes_mobile_ad_2"><script>propertag.cmd.push(function() { proper_display('tvtropes_mobile_ad_2'); })</script></div></div><h2>Provides Examples Of:</h2><p></p><ul><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AbsoluteCleavage" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AbsoluteCleavage">Absolute Cleavage</a>: Madoka's kimono manages to loosen in the ping pong match.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AccidentalKiss" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AccidentalKiss">Accidental Kiss</a>: Kazuma and Ui at the riverbank.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ADayInTheLimelight" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ADayInTheLimelight">A Day in the Limelight</a>: Daigo gets the center of attention in the OVA, and his various attempts to hook up with the girls...and <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DudeLooksLikeALady" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DudeLooksLikeALady">Ayumu</a>...</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AmusingInjuries" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AmusingInjuries">Amusing Injuries</a>: After Ibuki kicks Kazuma in the face in the first episode, he has a boot print on his face for the next few moments.</li><li> <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AnguishedDeclarationOfLove" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AnguishedDeclarationOfLove">Anguished Declaration of Love</a>: When Kazuma and Ui eventually express their feelings for each other in the <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/UsefulNotes/Tanabata" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/UsefulNotes/Tanabata">Futogoyama</a> festival at the end of the anime. <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheyDo" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheyDo">They end up together.</a></span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ACupAngst" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ACupAngst">A-Cup Angst</a>: Ibuki Hinata pats her chest in episode 6 after seeing the other girl's bosoms.<ul><li> Then there's her rather violent reactions to when Kazuma implies or hints it (eg see <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ThanksForTheMammary" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ThanksForTheMammary">Thanks for the Mammary</a> below for a hilarious example). More blatant is during <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Kazuma and Ibuki's date in episode 11, when at the shopping mall Ibuki tries on several outfits for Kazuma to see. One is a bikini. Kazuma looks at her chest and expresses disappointment. Cue <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LittleGirlsKickShins" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LittleGirlsKickShins">kick to the shin</a>.</span></li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AmazinglyEmbarrassingParents" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AmazinglyEmbarrassingParents">Amazingly Embarrassing Parents</a>:<ul><div class="proper-ad-unit mobile-ad square_ad"><h6 class="ad-caption">Advertisement:</h6><div id="proper-ad-tvtropes_mobile_ad_3"><script>propertag.cmd.push(function() { proper_display('tvtropes_mobile_ad_3'); })</script></div></div><li> Hina lampshades this with regards to her <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OverProtectiveDad" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OverProtectiveDad">Over Protective Dad</a> when he yells at her from the crowd to win the Hikonan Race.</li><li> Subverted: <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> just before the Tug-of-War match between Kazuma and Hina's dad, three of the mothers (those of Hina, Ui, and Madoka) gossip out loud about how good looking Kazuma is, and Hina's mom even wonders out loud if he's a good candidate to be Hina's husband. Naturally, Kazuma is not amused.</span></li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AmusingInjuries" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AmusingInjuries">Amusing Injuries</a>: Due to Hina's <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HugeSchoolgirl" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HugeSchoolgirl">height</a>, she hits her head on the ceiling of Kazuma's bedroom off camera with a very loud thud that gets his attention (right after <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HypocriticalHumor" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HypocriticalHumor">he warned her of the low ceiling</a>). A moment later she's seen squatting and clutching her head.<ul><li> <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">During the OVA when Ibuki invites Daigo to "go out" with her and he only ends up being her <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WilliamTelling" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WilliamTelling">target practice victim</a>, he sports a small bandage on both the front and back of his head!</span></li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AnimeHair" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AnimeHair">Anime Hair</a><ul><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShounenHair" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShounenHair">Shounen Hair</a>: Bad enough to parody. <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Kazuma's "hair" sticks up sometimes in the morning and Ayumu has to "handle" it. <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LiteralMetaphor" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LiteralMetaphor">Literally, of course.</a></span><ul><li> Daigo fits the trope better.</li></ul></li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AntennaHair" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AntennaHair">Antenna Hair</a>: Hina.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AnticlimaxCut" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AnticlimaxCut">Anti-Climax Cut</a>: See the <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DeathGlare" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DeathGlare">Death Glare</a> example below.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BeachEpisode" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BeachEpisode">Beach Episode</a>: Episode 8, with corollary <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SmashingWatermelons" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SmashingWatermelons">Watermelon Smashing</a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BearsAreBadNews" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BearsAreBadNews">Bears Are Bad News</a>: The first episode title (and Ui) make note of such. Kazuma was lucky he only ran into a monkey.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BerserkButton" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BerserkButton">Berserk Button</a>: Senka Yorozu feels greatly offended when Kazuma calls her <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MaamShock" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MaamShock">Oba-san</a>.<ul><li> Similarly, the three mothers <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">don't take it well when Daigo absenmindedly calls them "old hags"</span>.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BigBrotherAttraction" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BigBrotherAttraction">Big Brother Attraction</a>: Ui is very infatuated with her older brother, Hajime. <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Hence, when Hajime got married, she didn't take it very well.</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BigBrotherInstinct" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BigBrotherInstinct">Big Brother Instinct</a>: Kazuma. <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/JustifiedTrope" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/JustifiedTrope">Consider the fact</a> that his younger brother, Ayumu, is <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IllBoy" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IllBoy">rather sickly</a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BigEater" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BigEater">Big Eater</a>: Ui.<ul><li> Later on, Hina, justified that she hadn't eaten a single morsel ever since she ran away from home.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BishieSparkle" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BishieSparkle">Bishie Sparkle</a>:<ul><li> Used frequently on Hina, but also in a hilarious case with <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PuppyDogEyes" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PuppyDogEyes">Puppy-Dog Eyes</a> (see below). Also a few times on Ui when she's in a really good mood (like when she's about to <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BigEater" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BigEater">eat</a>).</li><li> Daigo uses it as an excuse to take pictures of Tsumugi in the OVA. Due to how sincere he seemed to be to have suddenly discovered an interest in photography, she buys it. Unfortunately for him, three older ladies also pass by, and when he accidentally calls them <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MaamShock" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MaamShock">old ladies</a>, they beat him up while Tsumugi goes home.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Bishounen" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Bishounen">Bishounen</a>: Kazuma, if comments from the mothers are anything to go by.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BridalCarry" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BridalCarry">Bridal Carry</a>: <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Kazuma carries Koyori to the finishing line in the Hikonan race. Bonus points for both of them wearing wedding costumes.</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BromanticFoil" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BromanticFoil">Bromantic Foil</a>: Daigo.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CallingTheOldManOut" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CallingTheOldManOut">Calling the Old Man Out</a>: Kazuma voluntarily argues the resident <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OverprotectiveDad" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OverprotectiveDad">Overprotective Dad</a>, Mr. Sakai, in Hina's stead to the point that he accepts the man's challenge to a duel in a tug-of-war match.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheCameo" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheCameo">The Cameo</a>: <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Minato Nagase and Yocchan from <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VisualNovel/AkaneIroNiSomaruSaka" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VisualNovel/AkaneIroNiSomaruSaka">Akane-iro ni Somaru Saka</a></em> make a cameo appearance in the <em>Hoshizora</em> Visual Novel, going on a summer training camp for their tennis club.</span><ul><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CanonImmigrant" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CanonImmigrant">Canon Immigrant</a>: <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Both of them appear again, alongside <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VisualNovel/AkaneIroNiSomaruSaka" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VisualNovel/AkaneIroNiSomaruSaka">Akane-iro ni Somaru Saka</a><strong>s protagonist Junichi, in the </strong></em>Hoshizora<em> fandisk, but while Junichi and Minato have their own little side-story within it akin the after-stories for </em>Hoshizoras heroines, Yocchan, as one of the headlining heroines (alongside former side-character Senka and new character Seira), actually gets her own route where she develops a romance with Kazuma</span>.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CannotSpitItOut" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CannotSpitItOut">Cannot Spit It Out</a>: Several of the girls are asked by the others what their relationship/feelings towards Kazuma are. They always give an ambiguous answer.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CantHoldHisLiquor" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CantHoldHisLiquor">Can't Hold Her Liquor</a>: Daigo's mom.<ul><li> In the anime Hina mentions that she can't even handle the <em>smell</em> of alcoholic beverages. In the Visual Novel, <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> at a party at the Yoruzuyo Inn during the summer festival she's persuaded by the guests to have some liquor, and downs at least a whole glass, and subsequently gets <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HilarityEnsues" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HilarityEnsues">completely wasted</a>.</span></li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CaptainObvious" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CaptainObvious">Captain Obvious</a>: The following exchange.<div class="indent"> <strong>Kazuma</strong>: So, [Hina] senpai, how did you end up this way?</div><div class="indent"> <strong>Hina</strong>: I ran away from home.</div><div class="indent"> <strong>Kazuma</strong>: <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BigWhat" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BigWhat">Ran away?!</a></div><div class="indent"> <strong>Hina</strong>: Running away from home means leaving without permission from parents or guardians, with no intention of returning.</div><div class="indent"> <strong>Kazuma</strong>: Yes, I know!</div></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheCaretaker" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheCaretaker">The Caretaker</a>: Ibuki for Ui, despite those two not being related.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CensorSteam" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CensorSteam">Censor Steam</a>: Literally, once, see <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NakedFirstImpression" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NakedFirstImpression">Naked First Impression</a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ChildhoodFriendRomance" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ChildhoodFriendRomance">Childhood Friend Romance</a>: Madoka is one of the available options in the game.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ClassRepresentative" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ClassRepresentative">Class Representative</a>: Ibuki, though she usually doesn't act like one.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ClingyJealousGirl" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ClingyJealousGirl">Clingy Jealous Girl</a>: Ui towards her brother's fiance in a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FlashBack" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FlashBack">Flash Back</a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ColorCodedCharacters" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ColorCodedCharacters">Color-Coded Characters</a>: Although they have vastly different personalities and looks, as evidenced by the trope picture, all the girls are easy to tell apart based on their hair color.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CoolBigSis" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CoolBigSis">Cool Big Sis</a>: Tsumugi.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CovertPervert" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CovertPervert">Covert Pervert</a>: Kazuma's imagination goes <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DoubleEntendre" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DoubleEntendre">wild</a> while playing an arcade <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RaisingSim" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RaisingSim">Raising Sim</a> with Tsumugi. Tsumugi isn't aware of that.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CrashIntoHello" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CrashIntoHello">Crash-Into Hello</a>: How Kazuma met Hina.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CryIntoChest" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CryIntoChest">Cry into Chest</a>: Visual Novel, <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> a plot point in Ibuki's path. When she starts <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HeroicBSOD" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HeroicBSOD">breaking down and crying</a> from not winning the archery tournament, Kazuma can choose to let her do this (in order to progress with her) or just let her cry on her own.</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CuteLittleFangs" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CuteLittleFangs">Cute Little Fangs</a>: Koyori.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CutenessProximity" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CutenessProximity">Cuteness Proximity</a>: Hina really has a penchant for cute little things in general.<ul><li> Gets brought up to <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HilarityEnsues" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HilarityEnsues">hilarious</a> levels during the Hikonan Race, when at the final stage where all the participants must wear a costume, she sees Ui dressed in a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EverythingsBetterWithPenguins" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EverythingsBetterWithPenguins">penguin suit</a>, and enters a sort of entranced/zombified state (and completely forgetting about her embarassment of wearing a skimpy <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Qipao" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Qipao">Qipao</a>) and pursues the latter at full speed (who gets really spooked by her pursuer and runs away).</li><li> Hina has started to show more varied reactions to the cute object/person depending on who or what it is. She acts like the <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CoolBigSis" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CoolBigSis">Cool Big Sis</a> towards Ayumu (and already <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PetTheDog" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PetTheDog">patting him on the head</a> at their first meeting), while she has a more suggestive reaction to when Kasane dresses up in a cute bear pajama suit (resulting in some bizzare sleep experience for the former when they spend the night in Kazuma's house).</li><li> Perhaps most amusingly, <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> after her <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OverprotectiveDad" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OverprotectiveDad">Overprotective Dad</a> lost a tug-of-war match against Kazuma, he ended up sulking, and somehow, Hina actually found it cute that she gave him a big bearhug</span>.</li><li> Happens to Ibuki, Daigo, and Ui when they first meet Ayumu in episode 2. They all immediately assume Kazuma isn't really blood-related.</li><li> <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Koyori</span> ends up as Hina's latest victim in the main series when she dons <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CatGirl" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CatGirl">cat ears</a>.</li><li> <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Ui's, Madoka's, and Hina's moms towards Ayumu at the end of the anime.</span></li><li> <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Daigo disguises him in a cat costume and she totally buys it. And before that, her reaction to a sleeping kitten has her <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DoesThisRemindYouOfAnything" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DoesThisRemindYouOfAnything">breathing heavily in a certain way</a>.</span></li><li> <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Ui is targeted again by Hina, when the former is dressed in a supposed-to-be-scary-but-actually-cute cat demon costume.</span>