n Kazuma has dinner she decides to wipe herself with wet tissues, and Kazuma walks in on her with her blouse and bra off.</span></li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NewTransferStudent" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NewTransferStudent">New Transfer Student</a>: The Hoshino brothers.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NoseBleed" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NoseBleed">Nose Bleed</a>: Daigo suffers from one in episode 8 when he <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ImagineSpot" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ImagineSpot">imagines</a> that Tsumugi is putting suntan lotion on Ayumu with her breasts. Unlike with the cheerleader outfit incident from episode 5, Kazuma punches him for even thinking that was what was happening to those two.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NotSoAboveItAll" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NotSoAboveItAll">Not So Above It All</a>: Daigo's mom sees Madoka's maid outfit lying on a bench in the OVA. She decides to try it on, only to have Daigo open the door to the locker room, and immediately close it again after seeing her. He tries to find some <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BrainBleach" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BrainBleach">Brain Bleach</a> immediately afterwards.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NotWhatItLooksLike" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NotWhatItLooksLike">Not What It Looks Like</a>: Kazuma <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AccidentalKiss" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AccidentalKiss">accidentally kisses</a> Ui in episode 1. Even after learning the truth, Ibuki still doesn't trust Kazuma.<ul><li> Unfortunately for Kazuma, it didn't stop there, becoming a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GossipEvolution" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GossipEvolution">Gossip Evolution</a> that spread througout the whole school (showed by groups of students talking about it when Kazuma walked by them), which Kazuma only found out eventually from Madoka.</li><li> <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Kazuma gets another one when Senka walks in on him in the morning with a sleeping Hina with her arms around him.</span></li><li> <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Daigo gets <em>two</em> instances in the OVA - first with Hina and caught by her <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OverprotectiveDad" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OverprotectiveDad">Overprotective Dad</a>, then with Ayumu (while the boy's in a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SchoolSwimsuit" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SchoolSwimsuit">School Swimsuit</a> to boot!) and caught by <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BigBrotherInstinct" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BigBrotherInstinct">Kazuma</a>, both cases <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ButtMonkey" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ButtMonkey">not ending well with Daigo</a>.</span></li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MaamShock" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MaamShock">Ma'am Shock</a>: The temperature drops when Yorozu gets called "Oba-san" (Auntie)</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OffhandBackhand" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OffhandBackhand">Offhand Backhand</a>: <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> At the start of Episode 12 Senka swats a bee this way with a wooden spoon while carrying on a conversation with Kazuma.</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Odango" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Odango">Odango</a>/<a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GirlishPigtails" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GirlishPigtails">Girlish Pigtails</a>: Koyori</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OhCrap" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OhCrap">Oh, Crap!</a>: Daigo has this look twice in the OVA. The first time is when he accidentally trips on top of Hina at her house, and her father happens to see them in the hallway like that. The second time is when he deliberately pushes Ayumu down after being overtaken by his <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/StupidSexyFlanders" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/StupidSexyFlanders">swimsuit outfit</a>, only to have Kazuma come out of his room, and then he does a throat slashing motion on Daigo. He understandably gets beat up both times.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OneDialogueTwoConversations" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OneDialogueTwoConversations">One Dialogue, Two Conversations</a>: In episode 2, after finding out that Ui bought a lot of cheese-flavored snacks, Kazuma mentions that something tasted like cheese. Ui immediately assumes it was her <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AccidentalKiss" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AccidentalKiss">Accidental Kiss</a> he did on her in the first episode, but then he clarifies himself and mentions the muffin she gave him for lunch had a hint of cheese to it.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OverprotectiveDad" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OverprotectiveDad">Overprotective Dad</a>: Mr. Sakai's not very approving of his daughter's desire to further her studies out of the village and into Tokyo University, even if it meant for the better of the entire Sakai household. He goes as far as to silence Hina when she speaks about it. Mrs. Sakai <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LetHerGrowUpDear" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LetHerGrowUpDear">advices him to reconsider his opinion</a>, as <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SheIsAllGrownUp" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SheIsAllGrownUp">Hina is all grown up</a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php