ing that they both have some feelings for him.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShipTease" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShipTease">Ship Tease</a>: <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Ayumu and Kazane in the Visual Novel, starting with a hilarious <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NakedFirstImpression" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NakedFirstImpression">Naked First Impression</a> in the onsen, followed by a cute conversation between them in the following scene.</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShoutOut" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShoutOut">Shout-Out</a><ul><li> "<a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/LightNovel/Oreimo" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/LightNovel/Oreimo">There's no way your little brother can be this cute!</a>" in episode 2.</li><li> Immediately followed by "If you're truly related by blood, this is a prank <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/TheWorldGodOnlyKnows" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/TheWorldGodOnlyKnows">God only knows</a>", to which Kazuma replies with "<a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CollectiveGroan" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CollectiveGroan">You people...</a>"</li><li> Episode 4 Previews: "She's like your <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/StrikeWitches" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/StrikeWitches">Strike</a> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IncrediblyLamePun" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IncrediblyLamePun">Uitch</a>, Oniichan!"</li><li> Episode 4's title is possibly a direct <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShoutOut" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShoutOut">Shout-Out</a> to the <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FluffyTamer" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FluffyTamer">Fluffy Tamer</a> scene in <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VisualNovel/AkaneIroNiSomaruSaka" titl