HiBye" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/StealthHiBye">Stealth Hi/Bye</a>: Parodied. Whenever Koyori makes the ram hand seal, she expects you to duck and cover your eyes until she leaves.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/StupidSexyFlanders" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/StupidSexyFlanders">Stupid Sexy Flanders</a>: A sizable portion of this show's <em>straight male</em> fandom are watching it for <em>Ayumu</em>, finding him to be cuter than <em>any</em> of the girls in the cast. Applies in-universe as well.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SugarAndIcePersonality" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SugarAndIcePersonality">Sugar-and-Ice Personality</a>: Hina.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SuperDeformed" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SuperDeformed">Super-Deformed</a>: Present in both the original <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/VisualNovel" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/VisualNovel">Visual Novel</a> and anime.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SupremeChef" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SupremeChef">Supreme Chef</a>: Ui's mother is apparently one. No wonder Ui loves eating.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SuspiciouslySpecificDenial" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SuspiciouslySpecificDenial">Suspiciously Specific Denial</a>: Ui, during episode 3.<div class="indent"> <strong>Ui</strong>: It's not like I wanted you to give me a piggyback ride, or have you feel my forehead...</div><ul><li> Kasane also says something about not taking pictures of Mugi-nee and selling them to men during episode 12, even though Kazuma never mentioned anything about it.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SustainedMisunderstanding" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SustainedMisunderstanding">Sustained Misunderstanding</a>: A few examples:<ul><li> In episode 9, Hina's father gets upset at her because she wants to go to a university in Tokyo. But up until this point, she never had a chance to explain why, either because he refused to listen to her, or something else came along such as customers entering their store.</li><li> In episode 10, Koyori at first wonders why Madoka is suffering from a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HeroicBSOD" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HeroicBSOD">Heroic BSoD</a>. Madoka's grandfather tells Koyori about the tug of war event from episode 9, and in the next scene, she storms into Yorozuyo inn, believing that Hina and Kazuma were getting married. Everyone there, including Kazuma, is quite surprised to hear about that.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SweetTooth" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SweetTooth">Sweet Tooth</a>: Ui and Madoka.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ThanksForTheMammary" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ThanksForTheMammary">Thanks for the Mammary</a>: Hilariously played with: <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> At the beach trip, Kazuma is blindfolded and asked to identify someone by touching them. He ends up groping Ayumu's chest, and then <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HilarityEnsues" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HilarityEnsues">guesses it to be Hinata</a>, who obviously doesn't take it well.</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ThePlan" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ThePlan">The Plan</a>: In episode 12, Tsumugi suddenly gets a bad stomachache before the ceremony is supposed to begin, prompting some emergency role switches between her and Ui, and having Kosane fill in for Ui's role. Madoka also writes something to put into the scroll. When Kazuma greets the goddess, he sees Ui instead of Tsumugi standing there, and is shocked at what Madoka had written in the scroll. <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Madoka had written "I love Ui" on the scroll, and as the credits roll by, Tsumugi claims she never had a stomachache in the first place, so several of them had <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShipperOnDeck" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShipperOnDeck">planned to use</a> the festival event as an excuse to get Ui and Kazuma together.</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheyCallMeMisterTibbs" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheyCallMeMisterTibbs">They Call Me Mister Tibbs!</a>: Daigo's mother, who's also his class' homeroom teacher, doesn't want him addressing her as "mom" while in class.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ThrowTheDogABone" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ThrowTheDogABone">Throw the Dog a Bone</a>: In the OVA, after failing to hook up with any of the girls, Daigo dejectedly watches the festival from afar. <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">A girl then approaches him, and tells him that she plays the female character in an MMO game they played together, and wanted to thank him for all the times he's helped her out in the game. She then asks him to the dance, and he agrees to it.</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TitleDrop" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TitleDrop">Title Drop</a>: Kazuma invoked it on episode 6 after listening to Ui talking about a well-known Japanese myth. He does it again at the end of the series.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TrademarkFavoriteFood" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TrademarkFavoriteFood">Trademark Favorite Food</a>: Ui <em>loves</em> cheese.<ul><li> Madoka mentions being fond of honey in episode 7.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TrainingFromHell" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TrainingFromHell">Training from Hell</a>: Senka tried to force Kazuma into this.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Tsundere" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Tsundere">Tsundere</a>: Ibuki and Koyori. Both were hostile to Kazuma when he first met either of them.<ul><li> Ibuki is called out to be a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Tsundere" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Tsundere">tsundere</a> by Daigo in the <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/VisualNovel" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/VisualNovel">Visual Novel</a> multiple times, and even goes so far as to ask Kazuma to hurry up and get to the dere side of hers.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TsurimeEyes" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TsurimeEyes">Tsurime Eyes</a>: Hina. Whereas just about all the other girls have <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TaremeEyes" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TaremeEyes">Tareme Eyes</a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TwoTeacherSchool" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TwoTeacherSchool">Two-Teacher School</a>: Daigo's mother is the only named school teacher shown in the series (the other is an unnamed male teacher shown in episode 2). Partly justified that each year level of the school only has one class.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/UncannyFamilyResemblance" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/UncannyFamilyResemblance">Uncanny Family Resemblance</a>: Madoka and Hina and their respective mothers, with slight variations.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/VaporWear" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/VaporWear">Vapor Wear</a>: Played with. <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> After the above <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NakedFirstImpression" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NakedFirstImpression">Naked First Impression</a> between Hina and Kazuma, Hina puts her blouse on after she's done cleaning herself, but forgets about her bra, which <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HilarityEnsues" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HilarityEnsues">Kazuma spots lying on the floor nearby</a>.</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WholesomeCrossdresser" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WholesomeCrossdresser">Wholesome Crossdresser</a>: Ayumu in a cheerleader's outfit. <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Even Kazuma approves.</span><ul><li> <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">In the OVA he wears a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SchoolSwimsuit" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SchoolSwimsuit">School Swimsuit</a>, and in the eye-catch that follows, a bikini!</span>'</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/YamatoNadeshiko" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/YamatoNadeshiko">Yamato Nadeshiko</a>: Tsumugi, complete with a kimono as she works at the ryokan. She also sets a secret plan into motion <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">playing sick so Ui can take her place as the Goddess at the festival.</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/YouGottaHaveBlueHair" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/YouGottaHaveBlueHair">You Gotta Have Blue Hair</a>: Just look at the page's image.</li></ul><hr>
</div>
